parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the Takata airbag can cause serious injury or death in the event of an accident, as the airbag may not deploy or may deploy improperly.
symptoms: Airbag warning light illuminates
airbag does not deploy in an accident
airbag deploys improperly
or the vehicle is recalled for Takata airbag replacement.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the airbag to deploy in an accident can cause serious injury or death, as the occupants may not be properly protected.
symptoms: Airbag does not deploy in an accident
resulting in injuries or fatalities.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the airbag to deploy in an accident can cause serious injury or death, as the occupants may not be properly protected.
symptoms: Vehicle is involved in an accident
airbag does not deploy
and occupants are injured or killed.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the clutch pedal assembly can cause the clutch pedal to stick to the floor, making it difficult or impossible to shift gears, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The clutch pedal feels soft or spongy
the clutch pedal sticks to the floor
the clutch pedal does not return to its normal position
the clutch pedal has a delayed return to its normal position
the clutch pedal has a sudden loss of pressure
the vehicle is unable to shift into gear.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The hard shifting and slipping of the transmission can cause the vehicle to jerk or hesitate, leading to loss of control, accidents, or damage to the transmission.
symptoms: The transmission kicks hard
the vehicle jerks or hesitates
the transmission slips or hesitates to engage
the vehicle shudders or vibrates
the transmission makes loud noises.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the Powertrain Control Module (PCM) or transmission electronics can cause the transmission to malfunction, leading to loss of power, hesitation, or failure to shift gears.
symptoms: The transmission hesitates or fails to shift
the vehicle loses power
the transmission makes loud noises
the vehicle shudders or vibrates
the transmission warning light comes on.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Premature wear of brake rotors can lead to reduced braking performance, increased stopping distances, and potentially cause accidents.
symptoms: Loud grinding or screeching noise when braking
vibration when applying brakes
brake rotors worn out excessively within a short mileage.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Brake line failure can cause a loss of brake fluid, leading to reduced braking performance, increased stopping distances, and potentially cause accidents.
symptoms: Spongy brake pedal
brake pedal feels soft
brake fluid leakage
grinding or screeching noise when braking.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Clutch failure can cause difficulty shifting gears, leading to reduced vehicle performance, and potentially cause accidents.
symptoms: Clutch pedal feels soft or spongy
clutch pedal sticks to the floor
difficulty shifting gears.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Brake judder and moan noise can be a sign of underlying brake system problems, which can lead to reduced braking performance, increased stopping distances, and potentially cause accidents.
symptoms: Loud juddering or moaning noise when braking
vibration when applying brakes.
